:::{#about-heading}

I am a researcher in English linguistics at Chemnitz University of Technology, working in the areas of second language perception and production, corpus linguistics and academic writing. 

Email: marina.ivanova[at]phil.tu-chemnitz.de

| Date       | News                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          |
|------------|--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| 16.12.24   | New review paper on training English word stress with technology at <a href="https://doi.org/10.4995/eurocall.2024.20400" target="_blank">EuroCALL Review</a>!                 |
| 10.07.24   | Happy to announce my new DAAD project <a href="https://www.tu-chemnitz.de/phil/english/sections/edling/research/scicom.php" target="_blank">"I, Expert: Media competence for science through linguistics"</a> in cooperation with the University of Zaragoza!                 |
| 21.05.24   | Excited for two new articles on "German English-medium linguistics journal abstracts over the last 30 years" and "English MA Theses at a German University before and after the Bologna reform" published in *TOKEN: A Journal of English Linguistics. 16*  (see <a href="https://mbisivan.github.io/pages/publications.html" target="_blank">Publications</a>) |
| 08.04.24   | I am happy to join the project <a href="https://www.smg.surrey.ac.uk/projects/declining-case-inflectional-loss-in-progress/" target="_blank">"Declining Case: Inflectional Loss in Progress"</a> (University of Surrey) as a transcriber of Bulgarian interviews.              |
| 01.04.24   | I am happy to join the TU Chemnitz English and Digital Linguistics team as a researcher (Wissenschaftliche Mitarbeiterin).                                                                                                                                                    |
| 02.02.24   | My PhD thesis on the perception and production of word stress cues in Slavic English varieties is now <a href="https://nbn-resolving.org/urn:nbn:de:bsz:ch1-qucosa2-892831" target="_blank">online</a>.                                                                        |



